  "summary": "metemask-sdk executes remote code from IPFS at import time",
  "details": "Typosquat of the legitimate metamask-sdk package. On `import metemask_sdk`, the top-level __init__.py fetches Python source from an IPFS gateway URL (https://gateway.pinata.cloud/ipfs/QmP2RrfNCNabLzPYncMGgFwAmttDafczpJLS8oxvQRBVqg), passes the response to exec(), and invokes a main() function from the fetched namespace, with errors silently swallowed. The exposed API (connect, sign_message, get_balance) returns hardcoded or random dummy values, so the package provides no real MetaMask SDK functionality — its only effect is delivering attacker-controlled code to any process that imports it. The IPFS object is mutable at the attacker's discretion and executes with the full privileges of the importing process.",
